<main class="Certify-landing--login-transition" id="main-content" role="main">
  <div class="Certify-landing--login-transition-hero">
    <div class="Certify-landing--login-transition-hero__body">
      <h2 class="Certify-landing--login-transition-hero__title"> You now need to create a login.gov account to sign in to Certify
      </h2>
      <h3 class="Certify-landing--login-transition-hero__sub-title"> To maintain your existing profile: 1. Use your existing Certify email address and 2. Create a new password.
      </h3>
      <form action="/users/auth/sba_idp" method="get"><div class="button_wrapper"><button class="button-full" type="submit"> Continue </button> to Login.gov</div></form>
    </div>
  </div>
    <p class="usajobs-landing--login-transition-sign-in__text">
      'Already created a login.gov account?
      <input type="submit" class="usa-button usa-button-gray usajobs-landing--login-transition-sign-in__cta usajobs-landing--login-transition-submit" value="Sign in" onclick="logPageUrl('Transition-to-Login-SignIn') ">
    </p>
    <p class="usajobs-landing--login-transition-terms">
      'By clicking "Continue" or "Sign in" you agree to our
      <a href="https://www.usajobs.gov/Help/terms-and-conditions/" target="_blank">terms and conditions</a>.
    </p>
    </div>
  <div class="Certify-landing--login-transition-faqs">
    <h2 class="Certify-landing--login-transition-faqs__title">
      'FAQs
    </h2>
    <div class="Certify-grid-full">
      <div class="Certify-width-one-half">
        <h3 class="Certify-landing--login-transition-faqs__faq is-first">
          'What is login.gov?
        </h3>
        <p>
          'Login.gov is a service that offers secure and private online access to government programs, such as federal benefits, services and applications. With a login.gov account, you can sign into multiple government websites with the same username and password.
        </p>
        <h3 class="Certify-landing--login-transition-faqs__faq">
          'What do I need to do?
        </h3>
        <p>
          'You need to create a login.gov account, if you don't already have one. <strong>Your old Certify username and password won't work anymore</strong>. You'll need to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Create a login.gov account - you only need to do this once.</li>
          <li>Enter an email address - <strong>use the same email address you use for Certify</strong> (your primary or secondary email address).</li>
          <li>Create a new password.</li>
          <li>Have a working phone number (mobile or landline) - login.gov will send you a security code.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3 class="Certify-landing--login-transition-faqs__faq">
          'How do I sign into Certify after I create my login.gov account?
        </h3>
        <p>
          'Every time you click <strong>Sign In</strong> on Certify, you'll go to the login.gov sign in page. You need to enter your login.gov email address, password and the security code that is sent to your mobile or landline phone.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="Certify-width-one-half">
        <h3 class="Certify-landing--login-transition-faqs__faq is-first">
          'Can I use my existing username and password?
        </h3>
        <p>
          No. You must create a new account with login.gov. This is a one-time step where you will use your existing Certify email address but must create a new password.
        </p>
        <h3 class="Certify-landing--login-transition-faqs__faq">
          'What email address do I use to create a login.gov account?
        </h3>
        <p>
          'Use your primary or secondary Certify email address, so we can automatically link your Certify profile to your login.gov account. If you use a different email address, we won’t be able to automatically link your profile.
        </p>
        <p>
          We recommend you don’t use a .gov, .mil or .edu email address. Instead, you should use a non-government email address. If you currently use a .gov, .mil or .edu email address for Certify, you may want to change it AFTER you get through the account set-up process.
        </p>
        <h3 class="Certify-landing--login-transition-faqs__faq">
          'What will happen to my Certify profile?
        </h3>
        <p>
          Nothing will happen to the information stored in your Certify account and profile. You will keep all of your information.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="https://login.gov/help/" target="_blank" onclick="logPageUrl('Transition-to-Login-LearnMore') ">Learn more about login.gov</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>